commit.message:
Updating URLs in the comments

Mostly migrating http to https, and linking to archived versions to old
pages that are now gone.

Swapping the order of numbers and characters in the legend.

Previously, the legend looked like this:
X   0 Y  10 Z

Which was counter-intuive. (see #6)

David (iamsudo) suggested putting numbers in the middle:

0 X 10 Y 20 Z

Which means that X is between 0 and 10, which maps precisely to the
prettyping behavior (in this case, 0 <= X < 10).

Hopefully, this will be less confusing. I think this also solves #6.
Mentioning the optional dependency on stty or tput.
Updating download URL from github.com to raw.githubusercontent.com

Merge pull request #1 from yggdr/master

Use /usr/bin/env for compatibility
Changing the label on Gratipay badge.
README: Changing header levels, adding a link to the latest release.

Removing the trailing dot, making it less likely to copy-paste the URL wrong.
